Using the change of base formula, we express each logarithm in terms of base 2023: \[ y = \frac{1}{\log_{2023}(7x)} \quad \text{and} \quad z = \frac{1}{\log_{2023}(289x)} \] Thus, the equation becomes: \[ \frac{1}{\log_{2023}(7x) \cdot \log_{2023}(289x)} = \frac{1}{\log_{2023}(2023x)} \] Taking reciprocals, we get: \[ \log_{2023}(7x) \cdot \log_{2023}(289x) = \log_{2023}(2023x) \] Let \( t = \log_{2023}x \). Expressing each logarithm in terms of \( t \): \[ \log_{2023}(7x) = \log_{2023}7 + t \quad \text{and} \quad \log_{2023}(289x) = 2\log_{2023}17 + t \] The right-hand side is: \[ \log_{2023}(2023x) = 1 + t \] Substituting these into the equation, we get: \[ (\log_{2023}7 + t)(2\log_{2023}17 + t) = 1 + t \] Expanding and simplifying using the fact that \( \log_{2023}2023 = 1 \) and \( 2023 = 7 \cdot 17^2 \): \[ t^2 + t(\log_{2023}7 + 2\log_{2023}17 - 1) + 2\log_{2023}7 \cdot \log_{2023}17 - 1 = 0 \] Since \( \log_{2023}7 + 2\log_{2023}17 = 1 \), the equation simplifies to: \[ t^2 = 1 - 2\log_{2023}7 \cdot \log_{2023}17 \] The solutions for \( t \) are \( \pm \sqrt{1 - 2\log_{2023}7 \cdot \log_{2023}17} \). Converting back to \( x \): \[ x = 2023^{\pm \sqrt{1 - 2\log_{2023}7 \cdot \log_{2023}17}} \] The product of the solutions is: \[ 2023^{\sqrt{1 - 2\log_{2023}7 \cdot \log_{2023}17}} \cdot 2023^{-\sqrt{1 - 2\log_{2023}7 \cdot \log_{2023}17}} = 2023^0 = 1 \] Thus, the product of all solutions is: \[ \boxed{1} \]
